
It's 2010 and time to sign up once again for your company's group health insurance plan. But this year, in addition to determining whether you want to pay for the high deductible, low deductible or HMO plan, you have to go to a Web site and answer a few questions. &#149; Has either of your parents ever been diagnosed with cancer, diabetes or heart disease? &#149; Have you ever been treated for a sexually transmitted disease? 

